The paper focuses on network representation learning, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories in computer science. However, given that the paper specifically addresses the problem of learning vertex representations for bipartite networks, it is most likely to belong to the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). Other likely sub-categories include Machine Learning (cs.LG), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), as these areas are also relevant to the problem of network representation learning.
